<p>I am using GAE 1.9.26, Thymeleaf 2.1.4.RELEASE and Spring MVC 4.2.1.RELEASE.</p>  <p>When my code is processing a valid template I receive <code>Error invoking operand validation in binary operation</code> According to comments in <code>BinaryOperationExpression</code> this </p>  <blockquote>   <p>// should never happen, would be a programming error</p> </blockquote>  <p>By analyzing the stack trace I have discovered that this bug is caused by GAE and its security restrictions:</p>  <pre><code>Caused by: java.lang.IllegalAccessException: Class com.google.apphosting.runtime.security.shared.intercept.java.lang.reflect.Method_$1 can not access a member of class org.thymeleaf.standard.expression.AdditionSubtractionExpression with modifiers "static"     at com.google.appengine.runtime.Request.process-bdfa726c8565882c(Request.java)     at sun.reflect.Reflection.ensureMemberAccess(Reflection.java:109)     at java.lang.reflect.AccessibleObject.slowCheckMemberAccess(AccessibleObject.java:261)     at java.lang.reflect.AccessibleObject.checkAccess(AccessibleObject.java:253)     at java.lang.reflect.Method.invoke(Method.java:44)     at org.thymeleaf.standard.expression.BinaryOperationExpression.doComposeBinaryOperationExpression(BinaryOperationExpression.java:178) </code></pre>  <p>Conflicting line where <code>leftAllowedMethod</code> is static:</p>  <pre><code>!((Boolean)leftAllowedMethod.invoke(null,leftExpr)).booleanValue()) </code></pre>  <p>Valid template that causes this error:           </p>  <pre><code>&lt;div th:if="${roles.contains('LICENSE_ADMIN') or roles.contains('LICENSE_ADMIN_LEGACY')}" class="form-group-button-row col-xs-12 col-md-2"&gt;       &lt;a th:href="@{'/firma_produkty/firma/' + ${companyIdentityId} + '/dane_podstawowe'}" class="btn btn-primary btn-insert"&gt;edytuj dane firmy&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="glyphicon glyphicon-edit"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Similar error with access to static resources by reflection on GAE is described here: <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/google-appengine/km_WJIBFTkA" rel="nofollow">https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/google-appengine/km_WJIBFTkA</a></p>  <p><strong>Questions</strong> How to avoid such a error? How to avoid usage of <code>AdditionSubtractionExpression</code>?</p>